Method Detail

reveal

void reveal()
Important: Do not call directly. Call ProxyPlace.reveal() instead. This way you can make sure you don't inadvertently reveal a non-leaf Presenter. Also, you will benefit from the change confirmation mechanism. (See PlaceManager.setOnLeaveConfirmation(String)).

Requests the presenter to reveal itself on screen. Upon being revealed presenters will ask to be inserted within their parent presenters by firing a SetContentEvent which will cause the parent to be revealed too.

prepareFromRequest

void prepareFromRequest(PlaceRequest request)
This method is called when a Presenter should prepare itself based on a PlaceRequest. The presenter should extract any parameters it needs from the request. A presenter should override this method if it handles custom parameters, but it should call the parent's prepareFromRequest method.

Parameters:
request - The request.

notifyChange

void notifyChange()
Notify others that this presenter has been changed. This is especially useful for stateful presenters that store parameters within the history token. Calling this will make sure the history token is updated with the right parameters.

onReveal

void onReveal()
Important: Make sure you call your parent class onReveal().

This method will be called whenever the presenter is revealed. Override it to perform any action (such as refreshing content) that needs to be done when the presenter is revealed.

This should never be called directly. Call reveal() instead.

prepareRequest

PlaceRequest prepareRequest(PlaceRequest request)
This method is called when creating a PlaceRequest for this Presenter. The presenter should add all the required parameters to the request.

If nothing is to be done, simply return the request unchanged. Otherwise, call PlaceRequest.with(String, String) to add parameters. Eg: 

 return request.with( "id", getId() );

A presenter should override this method if it handles custom parameters, but it should call the parent's prepareRequest method.

Parameters:
request - The current request.
Returns:
The prepared place request.
